Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Digital Circuits): The paper focuses on the design flow for M1 and contact layers, which are critical parts of digital designs. 
- cs.ET (Emerging Technologies): TPL is an emerging lithography technology that is becoming more important as feature sizes continue to shrink. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture): The paper proposes a framework for designing hardware that is TPL friendly, which could be considered a hardware architecture issue. 
- cs.EM (Electromagnetics): TPL involves complex electromagnetic interactions, so this sub-category could be relevant. 
- cs.VLSI (Very Large Scale Integration): The paper deals with the design of integrated circuits, which is the focus of this sub-category.
